text: Panther Creek is a stream in Bates and Henry counties of west central Missouri. It is a tributary of Osage River. The stream headwaters are located at and the confluence with the Osage is at . Panther Creek was named for the animal. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Bates County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Henry County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
title: Panther Creek (Osage River tributary)
